-- 
Warner Music Auction Involves at Least Five Bidders, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-08T05:57:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/warner-music-auction-involves-at-least-five-bidders-ft-reports.html
The second round of the auction for
all or parts of  Warner Music Group Corp. (WMG)  will involve at least
five bidders, including Platinum Equity and Ron Burkle’s Yucaipa
Cos., the Financial Times reported, citing unidentified people
close to the process.  Sony Music, BMG Music Publishing and Len Blavatnik’s Access
Industries Holdings LLC are already known to be in the bidding,
the newspaper said.  Yucaipa couldn’t be reached for comment and  Warner Music 
declined to comment, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 